For the guy in the last thread.

I have multiple long pieces of writing, including one at novel length, and I'd be fucking embarrassed to show them to anybody, and not just because of the subject matter. I've been writing for five years and haven't even tired to attempt something displayable outside of fetish communities.

Learning to write is easy, as in you don't really need to learn at all. There's no end goal aside from having passable spelling and grammar. Otherwise it's entirely a matter of creativity, planning and execution. Don't fucking pay for an online course, just write something, anything, even if it's shit. When you want to learn volume is more important than quality, those early lessons come thick and fast and you'll probably outpace your old work quickly.

And then keep going, personally I find posting them online very helpful because other people can pick out the faults that you're blind to. Even if people shit down your neck for your garbage, there's always something helpful in there. Every failure is a memorable lesson in not what to do next time.

Here's some baby mode tips though if you're really fucked up.
>The first thing you should come up with is your ending, knowing where your characters end up makes writing the path there easy as shit.
>Read other things, it can be literally anything as long as it has words in it, you learn a lot through osmosis.
>Watch other things, finding a theme you're passionate about is good idea fuel. What kind of stories do you enjoy most and what's the similarities between them.
>If you want to be a really big brain/dick motherfucker, read some books on narrative theory, understand the relationship between narrative, story, characters and themes and consider each element when planning something out. You probably won't need to do this if you're writing a story about Anon getting his dick sucked by an awoo though.
>Writing something sexy is a pain in the ass, don't get discouraged if you can't.
